Question: How to get substring based on special characters in android?: :Actually this is a very simple question, I tried a lot but I am unable to get the exact solution. I have a string like:String mystring = "one<1234567>,two<98765432>,three<878897656>";Here I want the data which is inside "<" and ">". Can anyone help me with this?
Please using this api: StringTokenizer.nextToken.
Answer:<<<api>>>: StringTokenizer
<<<code>>>: StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(mystring, "<,>");
String substring = st.nextToken(); // This will give you the data inside "<"
st.nextToken(); // Skip the data inside ">"
String substring2 = st.nextToken(); // This will give you the data inside second "<"
<<<explanation>>>: The nextToken() method of the StringTokenizer class returns the next token from this string tokenizer. The tokens are delimited by characters that are considered to be whitespace. The position is set to begin at the beginning of the next token.
Question: How to get the current date and time in Android?
Please using this api: Calendar.getInstance.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Calendar
<<<code>>>: Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance();
int year = calendar.get(Calendar.YEAR);
int month = calendar.get(Calendar.MONTH); // Note: This will return month as zero-based value (0-11)
int day = calendar.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH);
int hour = calendar.get(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY);
int minute = calendar.get(Calendar.MINUTE);
int second = calendar.get(Calendar.SECOND);
<<<explanation>>>: The getInstance() method of the Calendar class returns a Calendar with the current time and date. The Calendar class provides methods to extract the year, month, day of month, hour, minute, and second from the Calendar instance.
Question: How to create a custom list view in Android?
Please using this api: ArrayAdapter.
Answer:<<<api>>>: ArrayAdapter
<<<code>>>: ArrayAdapter<String> adapter = new ArrayAdapter<String>(this, android.R.layout.simple_list_item_1, myList);
ListView listView = (ListView) findViewById(R.id.my_list_view);
listView.setAdapter(adapter);
<<<explanation>>>: The ArrayAdapter class is a subclass of BaseAdapter that provides a binding from an array of values to ListView. The ArrayAdapter is an adapter that is backed by an array of data. The ArrayAdapter class provides methods to retrieve the number of items, get a data item, and get the data item id.
Question: How to create a custom dialog in Android?
Please using this api: AlertDialog.Builder.
Answer:<<<api>>>: AlertDialog.Builder
<<<code>>>: AlertDialog.Builder builder = new AlertDialog.Builder(this);
builder.setTitle("My Custom Dialog");
builder.setMessage("This is a custom dialog");
builder.setPositiveButton("OK", new DialogInterface.OnClickListener() {
    @Override
    public void onClick(DialogInterface dialog, int which) {
        // Handle positive button click
    }
});
AlertDialog dialog = builder.create();
dialog.show();
<<<explanation>>>: The AlertDialog.Builder class is used to create an AlertDialog. The AlertDialog is a dialog that displays a list of items, a single text field, a custom view, or an alert. The AlertDialog class provides methods to set the title, message, positive and negative buttons, and to handle button click events.
Question: How to create a custom toast in Android?
Please using this api: Toast.makeText.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Toast
<<<code>>>: Toast toast = Toast.makeText(this, "This is a custom toast", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT);
toast.show();
<<<explanation>>>: The makeText() method of the Toast class is used to create a new Toast that will display a single line of text. The duration parameter indicates how long to display the view. The duration can be either Toast.LENGTH_SHORT or Toast.LENGTH_LONG.
